187. Volcanum in cornu. The bombastic grandiloquence of these words at once recalls Pistol to the reader’s mind, a character of whom we are often thus reminded in Plautus. Lanterns were often made of horn in ancient times. Ussing quotes Athen. 15. 699f, κερατίνου δὲ φωσφόρου λύχνου σέλας.
